<h4 id="definition">Definition</h4>

<p>Process (noun): <em>a series of actions that lead to a particular result.<a href="http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/process&quot;">Âª</a></em></p>

<p>Progress (noun): <em>movement, as toward a goal.<a href="http://www.thefreedictionary.com/progress">Âª</a></em></p>

<h4 id="the-craft">The Craft</h4>

<p>One of the biggest challenges Iâ€™ve continually had in product design is finding a healthy balance between making progress to meet the destination set and truthfully crafting the product during the process.</p>

<p>We have all heard that cheesy quote, â€œitâ€™s not about the desination, but itâ€™s about the journey along the wayâ€. If we were to translate that into Product Design it would be so, â€œitâ€™s not about the end result, but itâ€™s about the process along the wayâ€. Following?</p>

<p>In the book <em>Mere Christianity</em>, C.S Lewis does an excellent job of illustrating how progress is directly impacted by the process:</p>

